<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 04-12-25 - New Articulated Piston Crown and Skirt</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi041225" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>04-12-25</tsinumber>
        <replace>
            <tsinumber>02-12-10</tsinumber>
        </replace>
        <tsidate>June 2004</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engine</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>New Articulated Piston Crown and Skirt</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>530E
                    <snrange>1194039 and above</snrange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>HT 530
                    <snrange>1194040 and above</snrange>
                </engfam>
                <engfam>DT 530
                    <snrange>1273511 and above</snrange>
                </engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <figure id="f04122501" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/H04026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Piston Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston pin</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston crown</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Piston skirt</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining ring (2)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>A new piston crown, part number 1826320C2 and articulated skirt part number, 1833433C1, has been
                    released as a service replacement for the original production piston crown and skirt. The new steel
                    crown design and bushing material are stronger, more resistant to long term lead sweating and
                    bushing pound out, giving it a longer and more durable life. Production engines beginning with
                    Serial Number 1365781 and above are built with the new piston crown and skirt.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To avoid damage to the engine, do not interchange the old piston crowns and skirts with
                            the new piston crowns and skirts. When replacing old piston crowns and skirts with the new
                            piston crowns and skirts, replace all six cylinders.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>Current piston service procedures apply to new designs (See service manual EGES-210). New run-in
                    procedures are required for the new piston crown and skirt. See run-in procedures instruction sheet
                    in the following kits:
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>IDENTIFYING FEATURES</title>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">Part Number 1836320C2</emph>
                        for new piston crown
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">Part Number 1833433C1</emph>
                        for new piston skirt
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <figure id="f021210" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/H04025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Piston Crown part number 1836320C2</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The new piston crown has the same size pads.</para>
            <figure id="f04122503" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/H04024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Piston Skirt part number 1833433C1</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The new piston skirt has a round surface at the pin bore.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
